WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.964 --> 00:00:16.731
[dramatic music]

2
00:00:33.197 --> 00:00:36.797
[dramatic music continues]

3
00:00:53.496 --> 00:00:57.031
[dramatic music continues]

4
00:00:58.098 --> 00:01:01.098
[wind howling]

5
00:01:01.197 --> 00:01:04.831
[dramatic music]

6
00:01:20.596 --> 00:01:24.197
[dramatic music continues]

7
00:01:33.897 --> 00:01:35.997
[coughing]

8
00:01:36.098 --> 00:01:38.362
[ship creaking]

9
00:01:38.463 --> 00:01:41.296
[wind howling]

10
00:01:55.997 --> 00:01:57.563
- Captain Walton.

11
00:01:58.463 --> 00:01:59.931
How's our visitor?

12
00:02:02.997 --> 00:02:05.864
- I've never seen a man in
so wretched a condition.


13
00:02:07.031 --> 00:02:09.596
He's dreadfully emaciated
by fatigue and suffering.


14
00:02:10.630 --> 00:02:12.997
Lord knows how long
he was on the ice.


15
00:02:13.097 --> 00:02:14.329
- Has he said anything?

16
00:02:15.697 --> 00:02:18.931
- Only nonsense, in rare
moments of consciousness,


17
00:02:21.362 --> 00:02:26.229
about a creature, a
demon, and a pursuit.


18
00:02:27.697 --> 00:02:29.329
[coughing]

19
00:02:29.429 --> 00:02:32.031
All we can offer him
now is rest and warmth


20
00:02:33.197 --> 00:02:35.031
and hope by slow
degrees he will recover.


21
00:02:36.997 --> 00:02:39.362
[ship creaking]

22
00:02:39.463 --> 00:02:42.031
[tense music]

23
00:02:50.831 --> 00:02:51.731
- Elizabeth?

24
00:02:54.097 --> 00:02:57.496
[tense music continues]

25
00:03:23.063 --> 00:03:25.731
[bell ringing]

26
00:03:29.597 --> 00:03:31.329
- [Buyer] Do you
have it with you?


27
00:03:32.797 --> 00:03:34.229
- That depends.

28
00:03:34.329 --> 00:03:35.630
Have you got the payment?

29
00:03:39.731 --> 00:03:40.731
- The diary.

30
00:03:42.931 --> 00:03:43.664
- It's in me bag.

31
00:03:43.764 --> 00:03:44.797
- Show it to me.

32
00:03:50.429 --> 00:03:52.931
- Ah, knew you'd be keen
as soon as I saw it.


33
00:03:54.731 --> 00:03:57.296
[tense music]

34
00:04:03.731 --> 00:04:04.864
- Remarkable.

35
00:04:06.030 --> 00:04:07.964
The author, this Frankenstein.

36
00:04:08.063 --> 00:04:08.897
- Dead.

37
00:04:08.996 --> 00:04:10.229
He won't mind it gone.

38
00:04:12.229 --> 00:04:15.396
- You said you saw the
creature, his creation.


39
00:04:16.630 --> 00:04:19.097
- Come on board after
I acquired the diary.


40
00:04:19.197 --> 00:04:20.296
Big brute of a thing.

41
00:04:21.329 --> 00:04:23.664
Tall as a man and
half, inhuman and foul.


42
00:04:23.764 --> 00:04:24.664
Ugly as sin.

43
00:04:27.697 --> 00:04:30.097
- You told no one
about our meeting.


44
00:04:30.197 --> 00:04:32.630
- Man like me knows
how to be discreet.


45
00:04:32.731 --> 00:04:35.864
Knows how to cover his tracks.

46
00:04:35.963 --> 00:04:37.697
- Yeah.
- Yeah.


47
00:04:37.797 --> 00:04:38.697
- As do I.

48
00:04:39.764 --> 00:04:41.963
[gasping]

49
00:04:42.063 --> 00:04:44.897
[dramatic music]

50
00:05:00.396 --> 00:05:03.897
[inhuman growling]

51
00:05:03.996 --> 00:05:07.630
[dramatic music continues]

52
00:05:30.163 --> 00:05:33.797
[fire crackling]

53
00:05:33.896 --> 00:05:37.362
[dramatic music continues]

54
00:06:13.097 --> 00:06:16.731
[dramatic music continues]

55
00:06:28.197 --> 00:06:31.229
[thunder crashing]

56
00:06:34.296 --> 00:06:37.229
[birds chirping]

57
00:06:40.963 --> 00:06:43.664
[gentle music]

58
00:07:31.297 --> 00:07:32.297
- Hmm.

59
00:07:37.497 --> 00:07:40.963
[gentle music continues]

60
00:08:01.597 --> 00:08:05.229
[electricity crackling]

61
00:08:18.863 --> 00:08:21.564
[bell ringing]

62
00:08:44.230 --> 00:08:45.763
[door closing]

63
00:09:05.363 --> 00:09:07.063
- Breakfast, ma'am.

64
00:09:07.163 --> 00:09:08.330
- You didn't need to
ring twice, Martha.


65
00:09:08.430 --> 00:09:10.363
There's nothing wrong
with my hearing.


66
00:09:11.564 --> 00:09:16.263
My love you, you've got
yourself up and dressed.


67
00:09:17.297 --> 00:09:19.896
- It seemed the
thing to do, my dear,


68
00:09:19.996 --> 00:09:22.297
with you working all night.

69
00:09:22.397 --> 00:09:25.664
- I'm sorry I completely
lost track, my darling.


70
00:09:25.763 --> 00:09:28.330
But you must take
care, you know, you,


71
00:09:28.430 --> 00:09:30.430
you could do yourself an injury.

72
00:09:30.530 --> 00:09:33.297
- God, there's nothing wrong
with the old boy really.


73
00:09:33.397 --> 00:09:34.763
I firmly believe his
body's giving up on him


74
00:09:34.863 --> 00:09:36.730
because you spend so much
time running around after him,


75
00:09:36.830 --> 00:09:38.297
he's got nothing to do.

76
00:09:38.397 --> 00:09:40.597
It's Mr. Darwin's theory
of evolution, you know.


77
00:09:41.763 --> 00:09:44.130
- What are you
doing here, William?


78
00:09:44.263 --> 00:09:45.963
Have you no food at your rooms?

79
00:09:46.063 --> 00:09:47.996
- Actually I have, Mother.

80
00:09:48.097 --> 00:09:49.763
I came to say goodbye to Clara.

81
00:09:49.863 --> 00:09:51.497
She's your daughter.

82
00:09:51.597 --> 00:09:55.397
She's, what is it
you're doing again?


83
00:09:56.497 --> 00:09:58.464
A week in the sticks
with Aunt Mabel.


84
00:09:58.564 --> 00:10:01.330
- We haven't got
an old Aunt Mabel.


85
00:10:01.430 --> 00:10:04.830
I am taking a month in the
country with cousin Jane.


86
00:10:06.497 --> 00:10:08.629
- And what pray are you
going to do for a month


87
00:10:08.730 --> 00:10:10.597
in the country with
dear cousin Jane?


88
00:10:10.696 --> 00:10:12.629
- Take long walks in the garden.

89
00:10:12.730 --> 00:10:15.830
Discuss single men in
possession of good fortunes.


90
00:10:15.930 --> 00:10:16.830
- Sounds wonderful.

91
00:10:16.930 --> 00:10:18.164
- I'm looking forward to it.

92
00:10:18.297 --> 00:10:19.464
- That's even worse.

93
00:10:21.696 --> 00:10:23.164
- Perhaps you should give
some thought, William,


94
00:10:23.263 --> 00:10:25.564
to your, your own romantic life.

95
00:10:25.663 --> 00:10:29.464
I hear the Hardy girl
has returned from Paris.


96
00:10:29.564 --> 00:10:31.696
Quite a pretty young
thing she is too.


97
00:10:32.663 --> 00:10:33.596
- Hmm.

98
00:10:33.696 --> 00:10:35.263
Perhaps I could marry
that lamp, Mother.


99
00:10:35.363 --> 00:10:36.763
It's just as
pleasing to the eye,


100
00:10:36.863 --> 00:10:39.497
but slightly more skilled
in the art of conversation.


101
00:10:39.596 --> 00:10:41.397
- If only you would attend
the Montgomery Ball.


102
00:10:41.497 --> 00:10:44.564
There are any number
of eligible debutantes.


103
00:10:44.663 --> 00:10:45.996
- So you can hang a
number around their necks


104
00:10:46.098 --> 00:10:47.164
and parade them like cattle.

105
00:10:47.263 --> 00:10:49.430
- I would like to see
a grandchild on my knee


106
00:10:49.530 --> 00:10:51.397
at some point in my life.

107
00:10:51.497 --> 00:10:53.963
- Mother, when you
become a grandmother,


108
00:10:54.063 --> 00:10:56.663
you'll hire a governess, put
her knee to work on your behalf


109
00:10:56.763 --> 00:10:59.464
and see the child twice a
year like you did with us.


110
00:11:01.464 --> 00:11:02.996
Kipper sandwich on the
bicycle, I'm afraid.


111
00:11:03.098 --> 00:11:04.464
I'm late for work.

112
00:11:04.564 --> 00:11:06.230
- Oh, that infernal contraption.

113
00:11:06.330 --> 00:11:08.663
And let us not even start
on the subject of work.


114
00:11:08.763 --> 00:11:11.230
A man in your position, it
really is quite beneath you,


115
00:11:11.330 --> 00:11:12.464
you know, my darling.

116
00:11:13.530 --> 00:11:16.131
- Do you know, I do so
enjoy our little talks.


117
00:11:16.230 --> 00:11:18.830
Funny how you remember
them word for word.


118
00:11:18.930 --> 00:11:19.896
Bye old girl.

119
00:11:21.330 --> 00:11:22.830
Try not to have too much fun.

120
00:11:24.198 --> 00:11:25.464
Father.

121
00:11:33.530 --> 00:11:35.497
- I suppose you think
I said the wrong thing?


122
00:11:35.596 --> 00:11:37.896
- No, not the wrong thing.

123
00:11:39.497 --> 00:11:42.896
Just the same thing
over and over again.


124
00:11:42.996 --> 00:11:47.430
Do you not wish for him the
happiness that we have had?


125
00:11:48.497 --> 00:11:52.330
Oh, let him find a
love match as we did.


126
00:11:52.430 --> 00:11:56.830
- My only wish is to restore
you to health, my darling.


127
00:11:58.464 --> 00:11:59.563
And so I will.

128
00:12:06.031 --> 00:12:07.363
- No, no, no no.

129
00:12:07.464 --> 00:12:10.363
She will not listen to
reason, Dr. Browning.


130
00:12:10.464 --> 00:12:13.397
Time and time again she
does only what she wants,


131
00:12:13.496 --> 00:12:16.563
regardless of my clearly
stated preferences.


132
00:12:16.663 --> 00:12:18.696
- Mr. Haddle, as I keep
trying to tell you,


133
00:12:18.796 --> 00:12:21.596
we are not a training
ground for errant wives.


134
00:12:21.696 --> 00:12:23.496
- She needs to be locked up.

135
00:12:23.596 --> 00:12:26.997
She's absconded twice
from sanatoriums


136
00:12:27.098 --> 00:12:28.763
and convalescent homes.

137
00:12:28.863 --> 00:12:31.031
I mean, what do you call
that if not hysteria?


138
00:12:31.131 --> 00:12:32.230
- I call it rather sensible,

139
00:12:32.330 --> 00:12:33.330
if you try to have her
locked up for writing-


140
00:12:33.430 --> 00:12:34.529
- What, poetry?

141
00:12:35.164 --> 00:12:36.330
It's a nonsense!

142
00:12:40.763 --> 00:12:43.263
- Your wife's frustrations
at the bounds you put on her


143
00:12:43.363 --> 00:12:45.430
appear to me to be the
very definition of sanity.


144
00:12:45.529 --> 00:12:47.363
Now if you will
excuse me, Mr. Haddle,


145
00:12:47.463 --> 00:12:49.230
I have patients to attend to.

146
00:12:50.463 --> 00:12:53.230
I fear in the hour
you've been here,


147
00:12:53.330 --> 00:12:55.463
one of them might have
written a limerick.


148
00:13:02.198 --> 00:13:03.496
- And sedate him, hmm.

149
00:13:06.064 --> 00:13:06.863
Haddle.

150
00:13:08.529 --> 00:13:09.863
Trouble, Browning?

151
00:13:09.964 --> 00:13:12.363
- For some poor woman,
Mr. Brammings, yes.


152
00:13:13.596 --> 00:13:15.363
- There's been another
complaint about conditions here.


153
00:13:15.463 --> 00:13:18.230
A member of parliament
has taken an interest.


154
00:13:18.330 --> 00:13:19.730
- What is it this time?

155
00:13:19.830 --> 00:13:22.529
The food, the cold,
the general conditions.


156
00:13:22.629 --> 00:13:24.696
- Do stop trying to guess.

157
00:13:24.796 --> 00:13:27.263
They should be grateful
to be here at all.


158
00:13:27.363 --> 00:13:28.596
They get bed and board.

159
00:13:28.696 --> 00:13:30.997
- They get tied to a
bed and bored stiff.


160
00:13:31.098 --> 00:13:32.796
We do nothing for them and
give them nothing to do.


161
00:13:32.896 --> 00:13:34.563
Sir, right now, in Paris,
Pierre Janet is doing-


162
00:13:34.663 --> 00:13:38.596
- Spare me another of
your theories, Browning.


163
00:13:38.696 --> 00:13:40.896
We require no
newfangled nonsense,


164
00:13:40.997 --> 00:13:43.830
we are in the business of
bed pans and sedatives,


165
00:13:43.931 --> 00:13:47.496
babysitting cast outs
and ne'er do wells.


166
00:13:48.429 --> 00:13:51.397
If you require an asylum

167
00:13:51.496 --> 00:13:53.230
run by a more fanciful
superintendent,


168
00:13:53.330 --> 00:13:55.098
there are many to choose from.

169
00:13:55.198 --> 00:13:56.429
Though none, I believe,

170
00:13:56.529 --> 00:14:00.031
that count your mother
among its trustees.


171
00:14:01.263 --> 00:14:03.863
Perhaps you wouldn't
like your chances there.


172
00:14:12.230 --> 00:14:14.863
[dramatic music]

173
00:15:02.529 --> 00:15:06.031
[dramatic music continues]

174
00:15:13.098 --> 00:15:13.997
- Ow!

175
00:15:15.964 --> 00:15:17.529
[rat squeaks]

176
00:15:28.864 --> 00:15:32.529
[dramatic music continues]

177
00:15:40.797 --> 00:15:42.696
[man grunts]

178
00:15:49.931 --> 00:15:51.263
- No you don't.

179
00:15:51.362 --> 00:15:52.596
- Get off me.
- Lie down.


180
00:15:52.696 --> 00:15:54.797
Settle down.
- Get, get off me.


181
00:15:55.897 --> 00:15:57.329
- What's going on in here?

182
00:15:58.763 --> 00:16:02.329
- Ah, here's a
young flap doodle.


183
00:16:02.429 --> 00:16:04.931
- What does it look like?
He's as drunk as ever.


184
00:16:05.031 --> 00:16:06.831
We come upon him with two
empty bottles in his arms.


185
00:16:06.931 --> 00:16:08.563
- Well where the devil
did he get those from?


186
00:16:08.663 --> 00:16:10.429
- One of the orderlies
would've brought them in.


187
00:16:10.529 --> 00:16:13.064
On a bribe or a favor,
it shouldn't be allowed.


188
00:16:13.164 --> 00:16:15.997
- Tell you all the ways!

189
00:16:16.098 --> 00:16:17.463
- Keep the noise
down, you old fool.


190
00:16:17.563 --> 00:16:19.463
- You can't speak to your old-

191
00:16:19.563 --> 00:16:20.529
- Quiet!

192
00:16:22.730 --> 00:16:23.997
You'll have Brammings down here.

193
00:16:24.098 --> 00:16:26.496
- [William] What's he in for?
- For his drinking.


194
00:16:26.596 --> 00:16:27.663
He's supposed to be drying out,

195
00:16:27.764 --> 00:16:29.230
and look what
you've done to him.


196
00:16:30.629 --> 00:16:33.496
- I may have had one
or two little nips.


197
00:16:33.596 --> 00:16:36.262
- I'll give you a little nip.

198
00:16:38.198 --> 00:16:39.797
- Oh!

199
00:16:39.897 --> 00:16:40.629
Liza.

200
00:16:40.731 --> 00:16:42.064
- Now get to bed.

201
00:16:42.164 --> 00:16:44.198
I hope your hangover blows
the top of your head off.


202
00:16:44.296 --> 00:16:46.229
- Now look here, nurse.

203
00:16:46.329 --> 00:16:48.296
We can't have you
assaulting patients.


204
00:16:50.064 --> 00:16:51.229
- What good are
you doing him, eh?


205
00:16:51.329 --> 00:16:52.731
I'd like to know.

206
00:16:52.831 --> 00:16:55.629
He come in here to get well
and he's as drunk as ever.


207
00:16:55.731 --> 00:16:57.731
- I'll have a word
with the orderlies.


208
00:16:58.864 --> 00:17:00.764
Perhaps I should
just set you on them.


209
00:17:00.864 --> 00:17:02.696
Might have a rather
greater effect.


210
00:17:03.997 --> 00:17:04.764
- I'm sorry.

211
00:17:06.429 --> 00:17:09.262
But is this supposed to
be a hospital or isn't it?


212
00:17:09.362 --> 00:17:12.131
- That's what some of us
are aiming for, certainly.


213
00:17:12.229 --> 00:17:13.864
- We're supposed
to be helping them.


214
00:17:15.262 --> 00:17:16.596
- Indeed we are.

215
00:17:18.897 --> 00:17:22.396
I say, are you new here, I don't
think I've seen you before.


216
00:17:23.831 --> 00:17:25.296
- I started 10 days ago.

217
00:17:25.396 --> 00:17:26.463
I'm Liza.

218
00:17:27.262 --> 00:17:28.596
- I'm William.

219
00:17:28.697 --> 00:17:30.262
Pleased to meet you.
- Yes.


220
00:17:30.362 --> 00:17:32.864
I know who you
are, Dr. Browning.


221
00:17:32.964 --> 00:17:35.596
It don't take 10 days for
our type to notice people.


222
00:17:41.329 --> 00:17:43.964
[birds chirping]

223
00:17:48.463 --> 00:17:50.664
- Ah, it's awfully quiet
here without old Clara.


224
00:17:50.764 --> 00:17:51.764
- Yeah.

225
00:17:51.864 --> 00:17:53.596
She's a bright young thing

226
00:17:53.697 --> 00:17:57.529
and of course your mother
is hard at work downstairs.


227
00:17:58.864 --> 00:18:00.764
- God only knows what
she's got planned for you.


228
00:18:00.864 --> 00:18:02.797
You know, I half expect to see
you stretched out on a rack


229
00:18:02.897 --> 00:18:04.396
every time I come home.

230
00:18:04.496 --> 00:18:08.229
- She is a remarkable
woman, your mother.


231
00:18:08.329 --> 00:18:11.831
If there is a cure for
me, she will find it.


232
00:18:11.931 --> 00:18:14.629
Had she been permitted
to sit examinations,


233
00:18:14.731 --> 00:18:18.797
she would've become an expert
renowned on the world stage.


234
00:18:18.897 --> 00:18:21.296
- Yes, while I do agree with
the woman question in general,


235
00:18:21.396 --> 00:18:24.296
Father, I fear in
my mother's case


236
00:18:24.396 --> 00:18:26.296
the world is rather
the safer for it.


237
00:18:27.429 --> 00:18:29.262
[bell ringing]

238
00:18:45.064 --> 00:18:46.964
- Lady Charlotte North, sir.

239
00:18:47.064 --> 00:18:50.496
- Colonel Browning, thank you
for seeing me unannounced.


240
00:18:50.596 --> 00:18:51.664
I had hoped to see you alone,

241
00:18:51.764 --> 00:18:53.630
this is rather a
delicate matter.


242
00:18:55.731 --> 00:18:59.262
- May I introduce
my son William?


243
00:18:59.362 --> 00:19:01.197
Do let him stay.

244
00:19:01.296 --> 00:19:04.964
He may be of some use, I
am rather limited you know.


245
00:19:05.064 --> 00:19:06.429
- Very well.
- Well this is


246
00:19:06.529 --> 00:19:08.229
rather unexpected.

247
00:19:08.329 --> 00:19:11.329
How may I help you,
Lady Charlotte?


248
00:19:11.429 --> 00:19:12.630
- I shall get
straight to the point.


249
00:19:12.731 --> 00:19:13.897
You have in your
possession a diary,


250
00:19:13.997 --> 00:19:15.429
I wish to have it in mine.

251
00:19:16.597 --> 00:19:17.563
- A diary?

252
00:19:17.664 --> 00:19:18.463
- It is of little value really,

253
00:19:18.563 --> 00:19:19.797
full of scientific fantasies,

254
00:19:19.897 --> 00:19:23.362
but there's some novelty
to the PT Barnum crowd.


255
00:19:23.463 --> 00:19:25.496
- Scientific fantasies.

256
00:19:25.597 --> 00:19:26.997
Perhaps Milicent can-

257
00:19:27.097 --> 00:19:30.764
- I represent a small group of
collectors of such novelties.


258
00:19:30.864 --> 00:19:32.463
- I can't help you.

259
00:19:32.564 --> 00:19:35.731
May I ask how you came to
believe it was in my possession.


260
00:19:35.831 --> 00:19:38.429
- We have ways of getting
information, Colonel.


261
00:19:38.529 --> 00:19:40.296
The group would be willing
to make you an offer,


262
00:19:40.396 --> 00:19:43.197
a very generous offer, far
in excess of its value.


263
00:19:43.296 --> 00:19:45.529
An offer unlikely
to be repeated.


264
00:19:45.630 --> 00:19:49.163
- You seem very keen for
something of so little value.


265
00:19:49.262 --> 00:19:51.097
- Well, you've been misinformed,

266
00:19:51.197 --> 00:19:52.831
I'm afraid, Lady Charlotte.

267
00:19:52.931 --> 00:19:57.831
I have no such diary and no
interest in any such diary.


268
00:19:57.931 --> 00:19:59.329
Perhaps my wife-

269
00:19:59.429 --> 00:20:00.997
- Your wife is unlikely
to be interested, Colonel.


270
00:20:01.097 --> 00:20:04.030
It is not concerned with lace
making and letter writing.


271
00:20:04.130 --> 00:20:05.897
- Oh, how little
you know my wife.


272
00:20:05.997 --> 00:20:09.197
- I must say, the nobility
seem rather less noble


273
00:20:09.296 --> 00:20:10.931
than we've been led to believe.

274
00:20:11.030 --> 00:20:12.731
- That rather settles it.

275
00:20:12.831 --> 00:20:14.597
I'm unable to help you.

276
00:20:25.931 --> 00:20:29.262
- I shall have that
diary, Colonel Browning.


277
00:20:29.362 --> 00:20:30.564
One way or another.

278
00:20:34.697 --> 00:20:35.731
- [Millicent] What
was that about?


279
00:20:35.831 --> 00:20:36.797
- Hmm?

280
00:20:36.897 --> 00:20:39.597
Oh, haven't the foggiest.

281
00:20:39.697 --> 00:20:42.664
I say, dear, you
haven't by any chance-


282
00:20:42.764 --> 00:20:43.897
- Are you sure
you'll be all right


283
00:20:43.996 --> 00:20:44.864
by yourself tonight, my love?

284
00:20:44.964 --> 00:20:47.030
I really do feel most
dreadfully guilty.


285
00:20:48.931 --> 00:20:50.897
William, could you
not stay the night?


286
00:20:50.996 --> 00:20:52.030
- What's all this?

287
00:20:52.130 --> 00:20:53.996
- Your mother has
an overnight trip


288
00:20:54.097 --> 00:20:56.864
in aid of her experiments.

289
00:20:56.964 --> 00:20:57.964
- I really must go.

290
00:20:58.864 --> 00:21:02.964
A rather promising
contact who has an item


291
00:21:03.063 --> 00:21:04.362
essential to my work.

292
00:21:04.463 --> 00:21:05.897
- Eye of newt?

293
00:21:07.564 --> 00:21:09.063
I've taken the night
shift, I'm afraid.


294
00:21:09.163 --> 00:21:11.262
The old boy will have to
look after himself for once.


295
00:21:11.362 --> 00:21:13.530
- Perhaps I should sleep
in the main house tonight-


296
00:21:13.630 --> 00:21:16.262
- I shall be perfectly fine.

297
00:21:16.362 --> 00:21:19.130
The only bother will
be how to occupy myself


298
00:21:19.229 --> 00:21:20.864
with so little happening.

299
00:21:27.464 --> 00:21:28.897
- The old boy go for your story?

300
00:21:28.996 --> 00:21:30.396
- Did he cop for having it?

301
00:21:30.497 --> 00:21:32.630
- We require an approach
with rather less subtlety.


302
00:21:34.296 --> 00:21:36.864
[tense music]

303
00:21:39.362 --> 00:21:41.996
[glass smashing]

304
00:21:54.396 --> 00:21:57.831
- Right, you look in here,
I'll go check the library.


305
00:21:59.163 --> 00:22:02.464
[tense music continues]

306
00:22:04.897 --> 00:22:07.530
[door creaking]

307
00:22:14.130 --> 00:22:17.530
[tense music continues]

308
00:22:41.731 --> 00:22:43.963
[glass shatters]
[Robert gasps]


309
00:22:45.296 --> 00:22:48.697
[tense music continues]

310
00:23:13.930 --> 00:23:15.229
- I say!

311
00:23:17.163 --> 00:23:18.731
Is someone there?

312
00:23:22.863 --> 00:23:24.397
- Didn't mean to
disturb you, guv.


313
00:23:24.497 --> 00:23:25.896
- What are you doing here?

314
00:23:25.996 --> 00:23:27.063
Get out.

315
00:23:27.163 --> 00:23:28.296
I'm armed, I tell you.

316
00:23:28.397 --> 00:23:30.597
- No, no, old boy,
just be civil, man.


317
00:23:30.697 --> 00:23:34.229
- Stay away or I shall fire.

318
00:23:34.330 --> 00:23:36.262
- I've gotta get to
the door, haven't I?


319
00:23:36.363 --> 00:23:37.996
If you're gonna chase
me from the house.


320
00:23:38.097 --> 00:23:39.963
Me all terrified and regretful.

321
00:23:41.797 --> 00:23:44.130
[screams]

322
00:23:44.229 --> 00:23:45.630
Where is it, old boy?

323
00:23:45.731 --> 00:23:47.229
- Where's what?

324
00:23:47.330 --> 00:23:49.530
- She says she wanted
something a bit less subtle.


325
00:23:49.630 --> 00:23:51.397
I reckon we should
give it to him.


326
00:23:53.697 --> 00:23:55.764
- Where is it?
- Oh, no, no.


327
00:23:55.863 --> 00:23:56.796
- You know what we want.

328
00:23:56.896 --> 00:23:59.630
- I don't!
- Where is it?


329
00:24:00.464 --> 00:24:02.030
[men laughing]

330
00:24:02.130 --> 00:24:03.262
Where is it?

331
00:24:04.764 --> 00:24:06.030
Where is it?

332
00:24:07.097 --> 00:24:08.330
Where is it?

333
00:24:09.363 --> 00:24:12.262
[dramatic music]

334
00:24:15.597 --> 00:24:16.530
- Robert.

335
00:24:17.996 --> 00:24:20.830
Oh my, my darling.

336
00:24:21.963 --> 00:24:23.664
- They were.
- Ssh.


337
00:24:23.764 --> 00:24:24.497
I know.

338
00:24:25.564 --> 00:24:27.564
I never should have
left you alone.


339
00:24:28.397 --> 00:24:29.330
I'm sorry.

340
00:24:31.731 --> 00:24:33.564
We should never be parted again.

341
00:24:36.963 --> 00:24:38.263
I promise.

342
00:24:41.731 --> 00:24:42.464
I promise.

343
00:24:48.130 --> 00:24:50.697
[tense music]

344
00:25:17.930 --> 00:25:20.564
[birds chirping]

345
00:25:34.097 --> 00:25:36.564
Please William, I won't have
you causing him any strain.


346
00:25:36.664 --> 00:25:39.297
- Damn it, Mother, must
you guard him so jealously.


347
00:25:41.430 --> 00:25:42.564
It's okay.
- Robert.


348
00:25:42.664 --> 00:25:44.796
- You're all right,
Father, I've got you.


349
00:25:44.896 --> 00:25:45.796
There we go.

350
00:25:46.930 --> 00:25:47.830
All right.

351
00:25:50.963 --> 00:25:53.830
You gave us a little bit
of a fright there, old boy.


352
00:25:55.796 --> 00:25:58.198
You've been out
cold for three days.


353
00:25:58.297 --> 00:26:01.363
- Sorry to have worried you so.

354
00:26:02.796 --> 00:26:04.063
And Clara.

355
00:26:04.163 --> 00:26:05.597
- She will arrive
in a day or two.


356
00:26:05.696 --> 00:26:08.263
I try to dissuade her but she
insists that she should come.


357
00:26:08.363 --> 00:26:10.763
- Just imagine the girl
wanting to see her father.


358
00:26:13.963 --> 00:26:16.330
Good grief, you look
a hundred years older.


359
00:26:16.430 --> 00:26:19.263
- Oh, I feel twice
that and more.


360
00:26:20.097 --> 00:26:21.663
- What were you doing?

361
00:26:21.763 --> 00:26:23.730
Taking the blaggards
on single-handed.


362
00:26:24.630 --> 00:26:26.497
- Thought I could take them.

363
00:26:28.363 --> 00:26:30.164
- At least you haven't
lost your fighting spirit.


364
00:26:30.263 --> 00:26:32.497
- Ha ha, the last
of it, I think.


365
00:26:33.597 --> 00:26:37.230
I feel rather closer
to the end of things.


366
00:26:38.663 --> 00:26:41.564
- You mustn't be
so morbid, Robert.


367
00:26:41.663 --> 00:26:44.164
- The old legs are done for.

368
00:26:44.263 --> 00:26:47.131
One of them is
turning gangrenous.


369
00:26:47.230 --> 00:26:49.464
I couldn't bear to lose it.

370
00:26:49.564 --> 00:26:52.597
I've been so reduced
over the years I, well,


371
00:26:53.730 --> 00:26:55.830
I want at least to remain whole.

372
00:26:57.164 --> 00:27:00.796
Perhaps my time has come.

373
00:27:03.097 --> 00:27:04.397
- No.

374
00:27:05.230 --> 00:27:06.564
My work.

375
00:27:06.663 --> 00:27:10.030
Robert, I am, I am so close.

376
00:27:10.131 --> 00:27:11.030
So close.

377
00:27:11.131 --> 00:27:13.430
- Let it be, Millicent.

378
00:27:14.198 --> 00:27:16.030
Let me go.

379
00:27:16.131 --> 00:27:17.363
- I won't hear it.

380
00:27:18.330 --> 00:27:19.497
I forbid it.

381
00:27:24.330 --> 00:27:26.796
- Oh, she loves me so terribly.

382
00:27:27.796 --> 00:27:28.830
- Terribly indeed.

383
00:27:30.796 --> 00:27:32.464
It's a selfish love.

384
00:27:32.564 --> 00:27:35.363
A selfish, solitary
exclusionary thing


385
00:27:35.464 --> 00:27:37.230
to the expense of
everything else.


386
00:27:38.330 --> 00:27:41.131
- She loves you too,
you know, in her way.


387
00:27:41.230 --> 00:27:42.863
- As if her way
is not to bother.


388
00:27:47.830 --> 00:27:50.796
- I haven't told
you often myself,


389
00:27:52.131 --> 00:27:54.464
how much I love you,

390
00:27:56.363 --> 00:27:57.930
but I do, you know.

391
00:27:58.030 --> 00:27:59.596
[gentle music]

392
00:27:59.696 --> 00:28:04.464
I am in awe of the man you've
become, a better man than I.


393
00:28:06.763 --> 00:28:09.164
I'm so proud of you.

394
00:28:09.263 --> 00:28:11.996
I'm so wonderfully proud.

395
00:28:13.930 --> 00:28:15.464
Working when you needn't.

396
00:28:15.563 --> 00:28:18.730
Helping your fellow man
when you could waste the day


397
00:28:18.830 --> 00:28:23.896
on bridge, cigars, as
selfishly as the others.


398
00:28:24.563 --> 00:28:27.464
[gentle music continues]

399
00:28:28.497 --> 00:28:30.031
- How thoroughly un
-British.

400
00:28:31.563 --> 00:28:33.730
The Queen will have
dispatched her troops.


401
00:28:36.131 --> 00:28:37.596
- It felt the time to say it.

402
00:28:39.796 --> 00:28:43.330
I fear this may
be my last chance.


403
00:28:45.363 --> 00:28:46.930
- On the contrary.

404
00:28:47.730 --> 00:28:49.629
I want more of the same please.

405
00:28:49.730 --> 00:28:50.896
And regularly too.

406
00:28:52.930 --> 00:28:54.496
It simply won't do.

407
00:28:56.330 --> 00:28:58.031
You've got to stay with it.

408
00:28:59.330 --> 00:29:00.930
We need you.

409
00:29:01.031 --> 00:29:04.496
[gentle music continues]

410
00:29:10.997 --> 00:29:11.763
I'll be off then.

411
00:29:14.230 --> 00:29:16.763
- Yes, yes, that's fine.

412
00:29:20.796 --> 00:29:21.863
[William sighs]

413
00:29:27.596 --> 00:29:28.896
You may go too, Martha.

414
00:29:30.297 --> 00:29:31.496
- Ma'am?

415
00:29:31.596 --> 00:29:32.730
- Go home.

416
00:29:32.830 --> 00:29:35.730
We shall require your
services no longer.


417
00:29:35.830 --> 00:29:38.297
Yourself, the cook, the
housekeeper and the gardener,


418
00:29:38.397 --> 00:29:40.230
the whole meddling lot of you.

419
00:29:40.330 --> 00:29:42.263
I want you out by tonight.

420
00:29:43.997 --> 00:29:44.830
- But.

421
00:29:44.930 --> 00:29:46.330
But without notice, Ma'am.

422
00:29:46.430 --> 00:29:47.763
- You shall be paid,

423
00:29:47.863 --> 00:29:49.496
I'm sure you can find
yourself another situation


424
00:29:49.596 --> 00:29:53.930
or a workhouse or an alleyway.

425
00:29:58.031 --> 00:29:58.763
Now go!

426
00:30:07.964 --> 00:30:10.563
[Robert groans]

427
00:30:15.964 --> 00:30:19.696
Some warm milk to
help calm you my love.


428
00:30:19.796 --> 00:30:22.596
[thunder rumbling]

429
00:30:56.363 --> 00:30:58.830
[tense music]

430
00:31:04.997 --> 00:31:07.696
[dramatic music]

431
00:31:28.529 --> 00:31:31.629
[thunder crashing]

432
00:31:36.396 --> 00:31:40.031
[dramatic music continues]

433
00:31:55.964 --> 00:31:58.629
[Robert groans]

434
00:32:04.730 --> 00:32:07.864
[Robert screams]

435
00:32:07.964 --> 00:32:09.730
I had to, my love.

436
00:32:09.831 --> 00:32:11.131
I had to, you'll see.

437
00:32:11.230 --> 00:32:13.131
- No, you couldn't have.

438
00:32:13.230 --> 00:32:14.931
- I can save you!

439
00:32:15.031 --> 00:32:15.964
- No!

440
00:32:16.064 --> 00:32:16.931
- I can!

441
00:32:17.031 --> 00:32:17.763
- Get out.

442
00:32:18.897 --> 00:32:19.931
Get out!

443
00:32:24.131 --> 00:32:26.696
[vase crashing]

444
00:32:41.797 --> 00:32:44.362
[tense music]

445
00:33:11.831 --> 00:33:14.463
[dramatic music]

446
00:33:18.696 --> 00:33:21.362
- Robert!

447
00:33:21.463 --> 00:33:25.329
[dramatic music continues]

448
00:33:30.131 --> 00:33:31.629
No!

449
00:33:32.663 --> 00:33:33.563
No!

450
00:33:34.629 --> 00:33:38.296
[dramatic music continues]

451
00:33:42.764 --> 00:33:47.731
- That he whose existence
appeared a part of us all


452
00:33:48.563 --> 00:33:51.296
can have departed forever.

453
00:33:52.897 --> 00:33:57.362
That the sound of a voice
so familiar and dear


454
00:33:58.362 --> 00:34:02.697
can be hushed,
nevermore to be heard.


455
00:34:03.897 --> 00:34:06.463
[tense music]

456
00:34:52.897 --> 00:34:56.296
[tense music continues]

457
00:35:04.429 --> 00:35:07.229
[gentle music]

458
00:35:26.329 --> 00:35:30.831
- That was a sin to have
only us at his graveside.


459
00:35:33.197 --> 00:35:34.764
- She wouldn't be moved on it.

460
00:35:36.429 --> 00:35:38.031
She wants him to
herself even now.


461
00:35:39.296 --> 00:35:40.831
- I still can't
believe he's gone.


462
00:35:42.463 --> 00:35:45.429
He'd been ill so long you
could almost forget about it.


463
00:35:45.529 --> 00:35:48.362
- Yeah, I suppose the assault
brought things to a head.


464
00:35:49.630 --> 00:35:51.463
- I'm glad he died in his sleep.

465
00:35:52.630 --> 00:35:57.130
That it was peaceful for him.

466
00:35:57.229 --> 00:35:58.296
- Hmm.

467
00:36:00.831 --> 00:36:02.831
I wish we'd been able
to see him at rest.


468
00:36:04.931 --> 00:36:07.529
Mother was so quick to
get him to the mortuary.


469
00:36:08.362 --> 00:36:09.496
- Mother.

470
00:36:10.564 --> 00:36:14.964
Mother and I are
just alone here now.


471
00:36:15.063 --> 00:36:15.864
- Must you stay?

472
00:36:18.362 --> 00:36:20.864
There's nothing
here for you, Clara.


473
00:36:22.329 --> 00:36:24.229
Not with the old man gone.

474
00:36:24.329 --> 00:36:26.429
He was the heart and
soul of this place.


475
00:36:26.529 --> 00:36:27.463
What now remains?

476
00:36:29.063 --> 00:36:31.097
Just an empty shell.

477
00:36:31.197 --> 00:36:34.630
- I should remain, for
Mother's sake at least.


478
00:36:34.731 --> 00:36:36.864
- Do you think she'd take
the same care of you?


479
00:36:38.197 --> 00:36:39.897
Do you think she'd even notice?

480
00:36:42.697 --> 00:36:44.362
Oh, go back to cousin Jane's,

481
00:36:44.463 --> 00:36:47.797
go where there's some
warmth and feeling.


482
00:36:49.964 --> 00:36:52.429
- I shall have to withdraw
from the ball, of course.


483
00:36:52.530 --> 00:36:53.429
- Don't you dare.

484
00:36:54.764 --> 00:36:56.630
Father would want you to have
every chance of happiness


485
00:36:56.731 --> 00:36:57.764
you possibly can.

486
00:36:59.197 --> 00:37:00.997
You can go from cousin Jane's.

487
00:37:01.097 --> 00:37:04.229
You'll look lovelier than ever
next to that old wallflower.


488
00:37:05.964 --> 00:37:06.931
- And what about you?

489
00:37:09.897 --> 00:37:12.764
- Don't you worry about
me, old girl, I'll be fine.


490
00:37:12.864 --> 00:37:15.497
[gentle music]

491
00:37:25.731 --> 00:37:27.463
[door opens]

492
00:37:34.030 --> 00:37:36.597
[tense music]

493
00:37:57.063 --> 00:37:59.530
[glass shattering]

494
00:38:00.864 --> 00:38:03.931
[Millicent screams]

495
00:38:14.464 --> 00:38:17.262
[dramatic music]

496
00:38:46.831 --> 00:38:50.229
[electricity crackling]

497
00:39:02.030 --> 00:39:05.697
[dramatic music continues]

498
00:39:52.664 --> 00:39:56.329
[dramatic music continues]

499
00:40:08.930 --> 00:40:11.464
[Millicent grunts]

500
00:40:32.297 --> 00:40:35.963
[dramatic music continues]

501
00:40:52.063 --> 00:40:55.664
[dramatic music continues]

502
00:41:13.030 --> 00:41:16.530
[dramatic music continues]

503
00:41:52.363 --> 00:41:56.030
[dramatic music continues]

504
00:42:18.863 --> 00:42:21.530
[wind howling]

505
00:42:23.996 --> 00:42:27.397
[electricity crackling]

506
00:42:28.430 --> 00:42:30.996
[tense music]

507
00:42:45.497 --> 00:42:48.564
[footsteps echoing]

508
00:43:11.996 --> 00:43:13.363
- It's too awful.

509
00:43:14.730 --> 00:43:16.763
It's too awful to
even contemplate.


510
00:43:19.497 --> 00:43:20.564
- He cannot be gone.

511
00:43:22.330 --> 00:43:24.263
He would never have left me.

512
00:43:25.629 --> 00:43:28.297
- There's been a spate of body
snatches these last months.


513
00:43:28.397 --> 00:43:30.230
There's money to
be made, I'm sure.


514
00:43:31.896 --> 00:43:32.830
It's an outrage.

515
00:43:36.830 --> 00:43:39.363
- Have you retrieved any
of the poor souls taken?


516
00:43:39.464 --> 00:43:42.097
- Not that I'm
aware of, sir, no.


517
00:43:42.198 --> 00:43:43.597
We'll endeavor to do
our best, of course,


518
00:43:43.696 --> 00:43:47.397
but the truth of the matter
is he could be anywhere.


519
00:43:48.696 --> 00:43:49.430
Anywhere at all.

520
00:43:51.896 --> 00:43:54.397
[gentle music]

521
00:43:58.896 --> 00:44:01.763
- The Frankenstein
serum is working.


522
00:44:01.863 --> 00:44:05.063
You are growing stronger
than ever you were,


523
00:44:05.164 --> 00:44:06.996
but I have missed something.

524
00:44:07.098 --> 00:44:12.330
I was rushed when reattaching
your leg, I was clumsy.


525
00:44:14.098 --> 00:44:15.830
It will not heal.

526
00:44:18.263 --> 00:44:20.363
You need a new leg.

527
00:44:21.430 --> 00:44:22.430
A new body.

528
00:44:27.131 --> 00:44:29.030
In which you can grow.

529
00:44:29.131 --> 00:44:31.696
[tense music]

530
00:44:41.996 --> 00:44:46.297
[tense music continues]

531
00:45:09.297 --> 00:45:11.696
[Robert groans]

532
00:45:11.796 --> 00:45:13.464
This too has failed.

533
00:45:15.529 --> 00:45:17.596
What more do you want from me?

534
00:45:20.164 --> 00:45:21.763
What am I missing?

535
00:45:24.796 --> 00:45:26.397
Embalming fluid.

536
00:45:27.596 --> 00:45:30.230
Were they using
formaldehyde a century ago?


537
00:45:37.430 --> 00:45:38.763
[tense music]

538
00:45:38.863 --> 00:45:39.563
No.

539
00:45:43.064 --> 00:45:44.098
This may be it, Robert.

540
00:45:44.198 --> 00:45:47.297
You need a clean body.

541
00:45:47.397 --> 00:45:50.496
Clean and unpolluted,
a fresh body.


542
00:45:52.763 --> 00:45:53.997
Freshly killed.

543
00:45:59.997 --> 00:46:02.796
- I'm not sure there's
much point in going home.


544
00:46:02.896 --> 00:46:05.463
Have to set off for the morning
shift as soon as I get in.


545
00:46:05.563 --> 00:46:07.563
- I'm hoping for an
hour's sleep standing up


546
00:46:07.663 --> 00:46:09.463
so I don't crumple my clothes.

547
00:46:09.563 --> 00:46:11.198
- Could do with a shave and all.

548
00:46:11.297 --> 00:46:12.863
- Old Bramming
said about as much.


549
00:46:12.964 --> 00:46:14.796
No doubt the entirety
of Western civilization


550
00:46:14.896 --> 00:46:16.529
would break down if
a man were to appear


551
00:46:16.629 --> 00:46:18.263
with a bristle on his chin.

552
00:46:18.363 --> 00:46:20.896
- Be like the last days of Rome.

553
00:46:20.997 --> 00:46:21.930
- Yeah.

554
00:46:24.964 --> 00:46:26.730
Well, um.
- Well.


555
00:46:29.463 --> 00:46:31.031
- Goodnight.
- Night then.


556
00:46:32.763 --> 00:46:35.330
[tense music]

557
00:47:12.330 --> 00:47:15.563
[tense music continues]

558
00:47:42.198 --> 00:47:45.230
[dramatic music]

559
00:48:02.263 --> 00:48:04.997
[nurses laughing]

560
00:48:22.730 --> 00:48:23.997
- Is it true?

561
00:48:24.098 --> 00:48:25.463
Alfred.

562
00:48:25.563 --> 00:48:27.730
The girls said that
he, he passed away.


563
00:48:27.831 --> 00:48:29.831
But I say that there
must be some mistake.


564
00:48:29.931 --> 00:48:31.696
He was as healthy
as a horse, he was-


565
00:48:31.796 --> 00:48:34.931
- No, no, no, no, it's
quite true, I'm afraid.


566
00:48:35.031 --> 00:48:36.131
They found him this morning.

567
00:48:36.230 --> 00:48:37.463
- No.

568
00:48:37.563 --> 00:48:39.198
- His heart probably gave out.

569
00:48:39.297 --> 00:48:41.629
He must have given it
dog's abuse over the years.


570
00:48:41.730 --> 00:48:43.831
- There was nothing
wrong with his heart.


571
00:48:43.931 --> 00:48:44.763
Not with his heart.

572
00:48:50.730 --> 00:48:52.362
[tense music]

573
00:48:52.463 --> 00:48:54.596
He would've been all
alone when he passed.


574
00:48:57.529 --> 00:49:01.396
- Yes, it's, was
terribly sad, I suppose.


575
00:49:04.329 --> 00:49:05.429
- You suppose?

576
00:49:07.797 --> 00:49:09.864
That's just the problem
with this place.


577
00:49:10.663 --> 00:49:13.198
There's no understanding here.

578
00:49:13.329 --> 00:49:14.529
There's no kindness.

579
00:49:15.696 --> 00:49:17.230
We have our troubles, our lot,

580
00:49:17.329 --> 00:49:19.296
and we're whisked away
to the workhouse or here


581
00:49:19.396 --> 00:49:21.396
or jail or worse.

582
00:49:23.362 --> 00:49:24.864
No understanding.

583
00:49:26.262 --> 00:49:28.164
No thinking about us as people.

584
00:49:28.262 --> 00:49:30.463
No thinking about
what might help.


585
00:49:32.230 --> 00:49:33.730
What we might be feeling.

586
00:49:35.764 --> 00:49:40.663
- Liza, I had no idea you'd
formed such a bond with him.


587
00:49:44.463 --> 00:49:45.831
Would you like to see him?

588
00:49:50.064 --> 00:49:51.496
There may be an autopsy

589
00:49:51.596 --> 00:49:53.696
but I would say given his
age and history he prob--


590
00:49:55.964 --> 00:49:56.696
He's gone.

591
00:49:58.463 --> 00:50:00.764
- What do you mean he's gone?

592
00:50:00.864 --> 00:50:03.931
- God in heaven, can the body
snatchers have come here too?


593
00:50:04.031 --> 00:50:04.897
- Body snatchers?

594
00:50:06.164 --> 00:50:07.529
You mean he's been robbed?

595
00:50:09.229 --> 00:50:11.429
You were meant to be
looking after him.


596
00:50:11.529 --> 00:50:12.931
How could you let this happen?

597
00:50:14.229 --> 00:50:15.064
How could you?

598
00:50:15.164 --> 00:50:17.731
[hand slaps]
[Liza whimpers]


599
00:50:23.329 --> 00:50:25.997
[dramatic music]

600
00:50:58.897 --> 00:51:02.429
[dramatic music continues]

601
00:51:13.463 --> 00:51:16.229
[dog barking]

602
00:51:16.329 --> 00:51:18.764
[tense music]

603
00:51:31.764 --> 00:51:33.897
- You shouldn't be out
here at this time of night.


604
00:51:33.997 --> 00:51:34.764
Ain't safe.

605
00:51:36.362 --> 00:51:38.764
- I'm not sure I much care
what happens to me now.


606
00:51:41.098 --> 00:51:43.997
- I didn't know that your father
had been taken too when I.


607
00:51:46.163 --> 00:51:47.964
- Gave me a piece of your mind.

608
00:51:48.064 --> 00:51:49.496
- Do you wanna hit me back?

609
00:51:50.630 --> 00:51:52.429
- No, I suspect if we
were to come to blows


610
00:51:52.529 --> 00:51:54.031
I'd be much the worse for wear.

611
00:51:55.463 --> 00:51:57.296
- They said they'd
give me a plot.


612
00:51:58.997 --> 00:51:59.831
The church did.

613
00:51:59.931 --> 00:52:01.362
A pauper's patch.

614
00:52:01.463 --> 00:52:04.463
Somewhere I could stand and
pretend his body was in there.


615
00:52:08.630 --> 00:52:11.563
He was my father, Alfred.

616
00:52:13.163 --> 00:52:14.296
I was too ashamed to say

617
00:52:14.396 --> 00:52:16.429
and then ashamed of
how ashamed I was.


618
00:52:16.529 --> 00:52:18.697
- Oh God, Liza, I'm so sorry.

619
00:52:18.797 --> 00:52:19.731
- I know you are.

620
00:52:21.064 --> 00:52:22.229
It weren't your fault.

621
00:52:23.329 --> 00:52:24.396
He said,

622
00:52:27.262 --> 00:52:30.064
he said you were
decent with him.


623
00:52:30.163 --> 00:52:32.630
Treated him like a human being.

624
00:52:32.731 --> 00:52:33.764
Like a man.

625
00:52:34.496 --> 00:52:36.229
Which is what he was.

626
00:52:36.329 --> 00:52:38.731
[Liza sobs]

627
00:52:59.864 --> 00:53:02.529
[gentle music]

628
00:53:05.362 --> 00:53:07.463
No need to walk me home.

629
00:53:07.564 --> 00:53:08.630
I know these
streets well enough.


630
00:53:08.731 --> 00:53:11.329
- Well then, let's say
you're walking me home.


631
00:53:16.697 --> 00:53:19.831
How is it you've done so
well for yourself, Liza?


632
00:53:21.163 --> 00:53:23.429
- We'd all do well,
given the chance.


633
00:53:24.697 --> 00:53:27.163
These people aren't here
because they drink and do wrong.


634
00:53:27.262 --> 00:53:29.630
They drink and do wrong
'cause they're here.


635
00:53:29.731 --> 00:53:31.530
And it's not us
which puts us here.


636
00:53:32.731 --> 00:53:35.097
You don't let us live, your lot.

637
00:53:35.197 --> 00:53:36.797
Not the whole of our lives.

638
00:53:36.897 --> 00:53:38.564
Not like we want them lived.

639
00:53:39.630 --> 00:53:42.030
You use our men's
bodies for their work,


640
00:53:42.130 --> 00:53:44.496
our women's bodies
for your amusement.


641
00:53:46.630 --> 00:53:49.564
I've clawed my way up a little,
but a little's all it is.


642
00:53:50.362 --> 00:53:52.897
[gentle music]

643
00:53:54.897 --> 00:53:56.362
- I think you're remarkable.

644
00:54:01.296 --> 00:54:03.497
I mean to find the people
that did this to us.


645
00:54:05.296 --> 00:54:06.764
To your father and to mine.

646
00:54:09.931 --> 00:54:10.831
- I do and all.

647
00:54:12.964 --> 00:54:14.063
I keep wandering around here

648
00:54:14.163 --> 00:54:15.897
as if I might catch
someone at it.


649
00:54:16.864 --> 00:54:17.731
- So do I.

650
00:54:20.163 --> 00:54:22.597
We should go in on it together.

651
00:54:24.362 --> 00:54:26.229
Have you seen
anything suspicious?


652
00:54:28.996 --> 00:54:31.897
- Only you lurking in the dark.

653
00:54:35.497 --> 00:54:38.329
- I, I hope you've eliminated
me from your inquiries.


654
00:54:39.897 --> 00:54:40.931
- [Liza] Might have done.

655
00:54:46.764 --> 00:54:49.497
[clock ticking]

656
00:54:54.429 --> 00:54:57.329
[flies buzzing]

657
00:55:02.296 --> 00:55:04.930
[Robert groans]

658
00:55:06.296 --> 00:55:07.930
- Do you remember
when we were young?


659
00:55:12.097 --> 00:55:13.464
When everything was new.

660
00:55:15.697 --> 00:55:19.996
Before the children,
before setback and illness


661
00:55:20.097 --> 00:55:21.963
and, and failure.

662
00:55:25.930 --> 00:55:29.030
No one can have loved as we did.

663
00:55:29.130 --> 00:55:30.229
It was ours.

664
00:55:31.030 --> 00:55:32.530
We invented it.

665
00:55:34.030 --> 00:55:36.731
We were why people sing,

666
00:55:36.831 --> 00:55:40.963
why poets take up pen.

667
00:55:42.197 --> 00:55:44.930
[Robert groans]

668
00:55:47.097 --> 00:55:48.664
Where are you?

669
00:55:50.764 --> 00:55:52.664
Where have you gone?

670
00:55:59.097 --> 00:56:00.930
Are you in there at all?

671
00:56:01.030 --> 00:56:03.597
[tense music]

672
00:56:14.229 --> 00:56:15.831
We have to find you new bodies

673
00:56:17.464 --> 00:56:21.731
and bodies to replace
them when, when those rot.


674
00:56:21.831 --> 00:56:24.996
[tense music continues]

675
00:56:28.430 --> 00:56:30.731
Let the body's pile high.

676
00:56:36.896 --> 00:56:38.296
- Mrs. Browning.

677
00:56:39.863 --> 00:56:41.030
This is a surprise.

678
00:56:42.330 --> 00:56:44.130
- [Millicent] I'd hoped
to see you, Brammings,


679
00:56:44.229 --> 00:56:46.630
to talk over recent events.

680
00:56:46.731 --> 00:56:47.797
- Of course.

681
00:56:49.130 --> 00:56:50.030
Of course.

682
00:56:51.296 --> 00:56:53.464
I was very sorry to
hear of your loss.


683
00:56:53.564 --> 00:56:55.464
Of course you have
my condolences.


684
00:56:56.564 --> 00:56:59.163
Young William appears to
be bearing up bravely.


685
00:56:59.262 --> 00:57:01.464
- His loss is not on the
same scale as my own.


686
00:57:02.430 --> 00:57:03.963
- Quite, quite.

687
00:57:04.063 --> 00:57:05.363
Well, you wish to discuss?

688
00:57:05.464 --> 00:57:07.497
- Recent events, Brammings.

689
00:57:08.697 --> 00:57:09.930
- Well the
disappearing drunkard,


690
00:57:10.030 --> 00:57:11.863
have the trustees some concerns?

691
00:57:11.963 --> 00:57:13.297
I can assure you that-

692
00:57:13.397 --> 00:57:15.697
- I can assure you
I have no interest


693
00:57:15.796 --> 00:57:17.597
in the concerns of
the other trustees,


694
00:57:17.697 --> 00:57:19.863
or in the disappearances
of the wastrels


695
00:57:19.963 --> 00:57:21.262
that you house here.

696
00:57:23.930 --> 00:57:25.229
Nor in their lives.

697
00:57:27.330 --> 00:57:31.363
On that, I feel
sure we can agree.


698
00:57:32.363 --> 00:57:33.597
- Well I,

699
00:57:36.464 --> 00:57:37.630
of course I have, as you know,

700
00:57:37.731 --> 00:57:40.229
been rather at odds with
your son on the matter.


701
00:57:42.430 --> 00:57:45.363
As for the lives
of our patients,


702
00:57:45.464 --> 00:57:47.430
I would agree that many
of them are better served


703
00:57:47.530 --> 00:57:50.863
by the workhouse or the courts.

704
00:57:50.963 --> 00:57:51.963
- Or the gallows?

705
00:57:53.664 --> 00:57:57.497
- Well, in certain
cases, perhaps.


706
00:57:57.597 --> 00:57:59.430
- You have always
struck me, Brammings,


707
00:57:59.530 --> 00:58:03.130
as a man of ambition,

708
00:58:03.229 --> 00:58:06.030
of advancement.

709
00:58:06.130 --> 00:58:10.030
A man whose career would
not be slowed by idle gossip


710
00:58:10.130 --> 00:58:11.397
regarding female patients.

711
00:58:11.497 --> 00:58:12.830
- Now I really don't think-

712
00:58:12.930 --> 00:58:16.430
- A man who knows the value
of a sympathetic ally.


713
00:58:16.530 --> 00:58:17.664
- Indeed I was grateful-

714
00:58:17.763 --> 00:58:20.197
- A man who looks
for opportunity


715
00:58:20.297 --> 00:58:22.263
and yet knows when to look away.

716
00:58:23.330 --> 00:58:24.763
Against your ambition,

717
00:58:24.863 --> 00:58:28.730
against a considerable
rise in income,


718
00:58:30.996 --> 00:58:32.397
what do these people matter?

719
00:58:34.230 --> 00:58:37.230
What does one care
for the ants underfoot


720
00:58:37.330 --> 00:58:39.963
as one advances
towards greatness?


721
00:58:42.930 --> 00:58:44.896
What would it matter
if others were to


722
00:58:44.996 --> 00:58:47.996
leave this establishment
earlier than expected?


723
00:58:48.930 --> 00:58:50.063
- Quite, quite.

724
00:58:50.163 --> 00:58:53.130
You, you said a rise in income.

725
00:58:53.230 --> 00:58:54.763
- A considerable rise.

726
00:58:57.664 --> 00:59:00.630
100 pounds for each of them.

727
00:59:02.363 --> 00:59:06.097
- Their lives may be
worthless, but my cooperation,


728
00:59:06.198 --> 00:59:08.963
however, is not.

729
00:59:11.130 --> 00:59:12.297
500.

730
00:59:14.198 --> 00:59:15.297
- Very well, 500.

731
00:59:15.397 --> 00:59:16.430
- And only the men.

732
00:59:17.564 --> 00:59:20.896
- The women, Brammings,
shall remain untouched.


733
00:59:20.996 --> 00:59:23.030
- And any more idle gossip.

734
00:59:23.130 --> 00:59:24.464
- Will be silenced.

735
00:59:26.497 --> 00:59:28.663
- How nice to have
things out in the open.


736
00:59:30.230 --> 00:59:32.030
I must say, I thought
you only cold.


737
00:59:33.497 --> 00:59:35.430
I could scarcely have imagined
that underneath all that


738
00:59:35.530 --> 00:59:37.330
you were such a malignant bitch.

739
00:59:39.363 --> 00:59:41.230
Now what do you require of me?

740
00:59:45.063 --> 00:59:46.330
- An open door.

741
00:59:47.863 --> 00:59:48.996
And a blind eye.

742
00:59:56.164 --> 00:59:58.497
- So this is how you
lot spend your time.


743
00:59:58.597 --> 01:00:00.530
- Less glamorous
than you expected.


744
01:00:00.629 --> 01:00:03.464
- If I'd have known I would've
left my tiara at home.


745
01:00:04.863 --> 01:00:06.663
- It's not all it's
cracked up to be, you know.


746
01:00:08.530 --> 01:00:10.131
I feel like I've
spent my entire life


747
01:00:10.230 --> 01:00:11.497
running away from money.

748
01:00:12.996 --> 01:00:17.164
Finds you, somehow,
wealth and privilege.


749
01:00:17.263 --> 01:00:20.464
Just becomes expectation
and boundaries.


750
01:00:25.198 --> 01:00:26.896
I do realize how
spoilt that sounds


751
01:00:26.996 --> 01:00:30.663
and I know I'm very fortunate
to have these as problems.


752
01:00:30.763 --> 01:00:31.830
- Well it's better
than wondering


753
01:00:31.930 --> 01:00:33.830
where your next meal's
gonna come from.


754
01:00:34.930 --> 01:00:38.263
Though I am surprised
at how unspoilt you are.


755
01:00:39.330 --> 01:00:40.629
You're the only
person of your class


756
01:00:40.730 --> 01:00:42.830
who I've not wanted
to kick in the knee.


757
01:00:44.297 --> 01:00:45.263
- You did punch me in the face.

758
01:00:45.363 --> 01:00:46.763
- That's what I'm saying.

759
01:00:50.397 --> 01:00:53.164
- My father was very
keen for me to understand


760
01:00:53.263 --> 01:00:54.763
the true value of money.

761
01:00:56.030 --> 01:00:59.397
Its limitations, that there
are many more important things.


762
01:01:02.696 --> 01:01:05.164
- You really loved
him, didn't you?


763
01:01:05.263 --> 01:01:06.397
Your father.

764
01:01:10.330 --> 01:01:12.830
- Yeah, I did.

765
01:01:15.230 --> 01:01:17.497
He was a very good man.

766
01:01:20.996 --> 01:01:23.796
- Mine was flawed,

767
01:01:27.330 --> 01:01:29.430
but I loved him all the same.

768
01:01:30.930 --> 01:01:32.930
- I wonder where they are now.

769
01:01:33.030 --> 01:01:34.530
- We'll find them.

770
01:01:34.629 --> 01:01:36.198
Though whoever's took
them's getting themselves


771
01:01:36.297 --> 01:01:38.497
a steady supply of bodies.

772
01:01:38.596 --> 01:01:39.896
- I'd say that's a thing.

773
01:01:42.198 --> 01:01:43.297
Where there's supply.

774
01:01:44.930 --> 01:01:46.430
- There's demand.

775
01:01:48.330 --> 01:01:50.996
[upbeat music]

