01:01:55.230 --> 01:01:59.464
[voices talking
amongst each other]


777
01:02:09.330 --> 01:02:10.230
Oh no, no.

778
01:02:10.330 --> 01:02:11.763
Thank you very much.

779
01:02:11.863 --> 01:02:15.330
[upbeat music continues]

780
01:02:23.164 --> 01:02:25.098
Are, are you sure
he's going to turn up?


781
01:02:25.198 --> 01:02:26.596
- He'll be here.

782
01:02:32.696 --> 01:02:35.496
- I'm beginning to feel a
bit like Sherlock Holmes.


783
01:02:35.596 --> 01:02:37.397
- I had someone else
in mind for you.


784
01:02:38.663 --> 01:02:39.230
There he is.

785
01:02:39.330 --> 01:02:40.397
Jasper!

786
01:02:41.863 --> 01:02:42.596
Jasper.

787
01:02:45.131 --> 01:02:46.230
- Liza!

788
01:02:47.830 --> 01:02:50.997
- Good to see you,
you old pile of bones.


789
01:02:51.098 --> 01:02:52.997
- I ain't seen you in a while.

790
01:02:53.098 --> 01:02:53.997
- Been working.

791
01:02:54.098 --> 01:02:54.997
- I'd heard.

792
01:02:55.098 --> 01:02:56.230
That's a shame for you.

793
01:02:58.164 --> 01:03:00.796
And I heard your
old man got took.


794
01:03:00.896 --> 01:03:03.930
Ah, poor old Alfred.

795
01:03:04.031 --> 01:03:05.496
He had many a time in here.

796
01:03:07.596 --> 01:03:10.031
I'll say this for
whoever took him.


797
01:03:10.131 --> 01:03:13.463
Whatever they're doing to
him, he won't need pickling.


798
01:03:13.563 --> 01:03:14.596
Nah.

799
01:03:14.696 --> 01:03:17.429
[Jasper laughs]

800
01:03:19.463 --> 01:03:20.696
And who's this?

801
01:03:20.796 --> 01:03:22.931
Are you moving up in
the world, my girl?


802
01:03:23.031 --> 01:03:24.463
- This is a friend.

803
01:03:24.563 --> 01:03:27.896
Dr. Watson, from my work.

804
01:03:28.997 --> 01:03:30.563
- You've not come to
take me in, have you?


805
01:03:30.663 --> 01:03:33.496
I'll fight you before you
put me in one of them coats.


806
01:03:33.596 --> 01:03:34.529
I will.

807
01:03:34.629 --> 01:03:36.230
- His dad got took and all.

808
01:03:37.397 --> 01:03:38.463
- Did he now?

809
01:03:41.429 --> 01:03:43.297
Was he in the loony
bin with old Alfred?


810
01:03:43.397 --> 01:03:47.131
- No, he was-
- He got dug up.


811
01:03:47.230 --> 01:03:48.863
Proper sacrilegious it was.

812
01:03:50.663 --> 01:03:52.529
- I'd heard there was
some of that going on.


813
01:03:53.396 --> 01:03:54.529
- Well that's why we're here.

814
01:03:54.629 --> 01:03:55.463
There's nothing
goes on around here


815
01:03:55.563 --> 01:03:57.263
without you hearing about it.

816
01:03:58.596 --> 01:04:00.897
Or you having a
hand in it yourself,


817
01:04:00.997 --> 01:04:02.763
if you get whiff of a coin.

818
01:04:02.863 --> 01:04:05.131
- Oi, I hope you don't
think I'm involved


819
01:04:05.230 --> 01:04:06.496
in none of that, my girl.

820
01:04:06.596 --> 01:04:08.463
I've been known to buy and sell

821
01:04:08.563 --> 01:04:11.263
the occasional item of interest.

822
01:04:11.363 --> 01:04:13.730
Them what's dead should
be left in peace I say.


823
01:04:16.629 --> 01:04:18.596
I may not go by
every law of the land


824
01:04:19.663 --> 01:04:21.997
but the laws of God and
nature is different.


825
01:04:23.263 --> 01:04:24.931
- Maybe you heard
something about it.


826
01:04:25.031 --> 01:04:25.763
- Nothing.

827
01:04:27.763 --> 01:04:30.529
- Then maybe you could
inquire among your associates.


828
01:04:31.230 --> 01:04:32.496
- And ask them what?

829
01:04:33.529 --> 01:04:35.330
Anyone in the
market for a spleen.


830
01:04:37.429 --> 01:04:40.362
I'll tell you, I've
not heard a thing


831
01:04:40.463 --> 01:04:42.263
and that means
something, don't it.


832
01:04:43.330 --> 01:04:45.629
It means it ain't
one of ours doing it.


833
01:04:50.696 --> 01:04:54.396
Last round of body
snatching a few years back,


834
01:04:55.730 --> 01:04:58.396
they wasn't being taken for
food or for throwing on the fire


835
01:04:58.496 --> 01:05:00.131
instead of coal, was they?

836
01:05:00.230 --> 01:05:03.329
They was being taken
for men of science


837
01:05:04.696 --> 01:05:07.730
picking over their bones,
seeing what made them tick.


838
01:05:07.831 --> 01:05:10.463
[tense music]

839
01:05:10.563 --> 01:05:13.064
Alfred got took from
your place, didn't he?


840
01:05:13.164 --> 01:05:14.496
- Mm-hmm.

841
01:05:14.596 --> 01:05:17.031
- You wanna find
them what took him?


842
01:05:17.131 --> 01:05:19.964
I suggest you look
closer to home.


843
01:05:20.064 --> 01:05:23.463
[tense music continues]

844
01:05:27.831 --> 01:05:30.396
- Did you hear the
devil's footsteps.


845
01:05:31.429 --> 01:05:33.864
Click, click, click,
click it goes.


846
01:05:33.964 --> 01:05:37.296
I can keep traveling.

847
01:05:37.396 --> 01:05:40.529
[footsteps thumping]

848
01:05:43.931 --> 01:05:46.230
It's come to take me, hasn't it.

849
01:05:46.329 --> 01:05:49.296
Sit with them cooking in pantry.

850
01:05:49.396 --> 01:05:51.964
Walking in the square.

851
01:05:52.064 --> 01:05:53.797
Meant to dance.

852
01:05:53.897 --> 01:05:55.763
What a very nice time.

853
01:05:55.864 --> 01:05:58.629
[dramatic music]

854
01:06:11.730 --> 01:06:14.031
- There's been another
one on the fourth floor.


855
01:06:17.198 --> 01:06:18.198
One here and all?

856
01:06:18.296 --> 01:06:19.296
- Yes, I think so.

857
01:06:19.396 --> 01:06:20.064
What do you mean another one?

858
01:06:20.164 --> 01:06:21.563
- Do calm down.

859
01:06:21.663 --> 01:06:25.563
Two patients have
simply chosen to leave.


860
01:06:25.663 --> 01:06:27.864
- Two patients in restraints

861
01:06:27.964 --> 01:06:30.629
have chosen to leave
from behind locked doors.


862
01:06:30.730 --> 01:06:33.629
- Really, you must not
apply reason to madness.


863
01:06:34.362 --> 01:06:35.663
Is there any blood?

864
01:06:36.463 --> 01:06:38.429
Any disturbance?

865
01:06:39.396 --> 01:06:40.731
Any signs of a struggle?

866
01:06:41.797 --> 01:06:43.731
A struggle, Browning.

867
01:06:43.831 --> 01:06:45.663
Not poor housekeeping.

868
01:06:47.396 --> 01:06:48.463
- Mr. Brammings.

869
01:06:50.164 --> 01:06:52.031
Mr. Brammings.

870
01:06:52.131 --> 01:06:54.629
There's something desperately
wrong in this place, sir.


871
01:06:54.731 --> 01:06:56.797
First Alfred Dobson,
now these two.


872
01:06:58.031 --> 01:06:59.362
- I see no similarities.

873
01:07:00.696 --> 01:07:03.198
What happened with the
drunkard was unfortunate.


874
01:07:03.296 --> 01:07:06.429
But what you have this
morning are two empty beds,


875
01:07:06.529 --> 01:07:11.197
no bodies, and an
overactive imagination.


876
01:07:11.296 --> 01:07:13.563
- What you have
this morning, sir,


877
01:07:13.663 --> 01:07:16.362
is patients disappearing
on your watch.


878
01:07:16.463 --> 01:07:17.596
Now I know you
don't care anything


879
01:07:17.697 --> 01:07:19.098
about these people
at all, you old fool,


880
01:07:19.197 --> 01:07:20.362
but you do still have
a duty towards them.


881
01:07:20.463 --> 01:07:22.098
- Now see here, you jumped up-

882
01:07:22.197 --> 01:07:23.164
- Get off me.

883
01:07:23.262 --> 01:07:24.697
[Liza gasps]

884
01:07:32.296 --> 01:07:34.897
[tense music]

885
01:07:36.731 --> 01:07:39.897
We swore an oath to
these men, Brammings,


886
01:07:41.463 --> 01:07:45.496
to do them no harm and to
see no harm done to them.


887
01:07:45.596 --> 01:07:50.664
- And two empty beds aside,
there remain many more in here


888
01:07:51.764 --> 01:07:56.429
in need of your fussy,
nannying bedside manner.


889
01:07:57.797 --> 01:08:01.362
Now may I suggest
you learn your place


890
01:08:01.463 --> 01:08:04.629
and get back to work!

891
01:08:05.529 --> 01:08:08.931
[tense music continues]

892
01:08:12.262 --> 01:08:12.964
- Now what?

893
01:08:14.098 --> 01:08:15.596
What can we do?

894
01:08:15.697 --> 01:08:17.163
What with old
Brammings in the way?


895
01:08:17.262 --> 01:08:20.197
[tense music continues]

896
01:08:20.296 --> 01:08:22.529
- Now we go over his head.

897
01:08:24.262 --> 01:08:25.997
We go to the trustees.

898
01:08:27.163 --> 01:08:29.130
Mother!

899
01:08:29.229 --> 01:08:32.630
[tense music continues]

900
01:08:37.262 --> 01:08:39.831
[flies buzzing]

901
01:08:54.329 --> 01:08:55.931
Mother!

902
01:08:56.031 --> 01:08:58.764
[clock ticking]

903
01:09:06.931 --> 01:09:09.864
[tense music continues]

904
01:09:16.496 --> 01:09:18.797
[thumping on door]

905
01:09:22.229 --> 01:09:22.964
Mother!

906
01:09:25.197 --> 01:09:27.463
[thumping on door continues]

907
01:09:27.564 --> 01:09:28.463
Mother!

908
01:09:39.329 --> 01:09:41.329
- [Millicent] What
are you doing here?


909
01:09:43.664 --> 01:09:45.329
- Are you quite
all right, Mother?


910
01:09:45.429 --> 01:09:46.496
Where are the staff?

911
01:09:47.496 --> 01:09:48.797
- I have dismissed them.

912
01:09:48.897 --> 01:09:50.831
I no longer require
their services.


913
01:09:52.831 --> 01:09:54.864
- It would appear you
have a very great need


914
01:09:54.964 --> 01:09:56.030
of their services.

915
01:09:56.130 --> 01:09:57.864
- I have been
rather preoccupied.


916
01:09:57.964 --> 01:10:01.030
I will get to these
things this afternoon.


917
01:10:02.130 --> 01:10:05.229
[tense music]

918
01:10:05.329 --> 01:10:06.296
- Let me help you.

919
01:10:08.931 --> 01:10:10.864
- I prefer to be alone.

920
01:10:10.964 --> 01:10:11.831
- Of course.

921
01:10:13.564 --> 01:10:14.731
But with Father gone.

922
01:10:14.831 --> 01:10:16.831
- I asked you what
you're doing here.


923
01:10:16.931 --> 01:10:20.329
[tense music continues]

924
01:10:21.897 --> 01:10:23.229
- Fear not.

925
01:10:24.731 --> 01:10:26.597
I come in a purely
professional capacity.


926
01:10:26.697 --> 01:10:28.063
There's trouble at the asylum.

927
01:10:28.163 --> 01:10:30.296
- Then I suggest you
speak to Mr. Brammings.


928
01:10:30.396 --> 01:10:31.262
- I have.

929
01:10:33.396 --> 01:10:34.463
There have been disappearances,

930
01:10:34.564 --> 01:10:36.362
he shows very little interest.

931
01:10:36.463 --> 01:10:38.396
- I can assure you I have less.

932
01:10:38.497 --> 01:10:41.597
- And yet you have
a responsibility
towards our patients,


933
01:10:41.697 --> 01:10:43.329
whether you care
for them or not.


934
01:10:43.429 --> 01:10:45.996
- What would you have me
do, become a night watchman?


935
01:10:46.097 --> 01:10:48.697
- I would have you call a
meeting of the trustees.


936
01:10:48.797 --> 01:10:51.831
Demand Brammings explain
himself and if he cannot,


937
01:10:51.931 --> 01:10:53.996
I would have you replace him.

938
01:10:54.931 --> 01:10:55.864
- Very well.

939
01:10:57.831 --> 01:10:58.964
- You will do so?

940
01:10:59.063 --> 01:11:00.329
- Certainly I shall.

941
01:11:00.429 --> 01:11:04.163
[tense music continues]

942
01:11:04.262 --> 01:11:05.963
- I'm fine by the way.

943
01:11:07.664 --> 01:11:09.931
And Clara too, she has written.

944
01:11:10.030 --> 01:11:12.630
[clock ticking]

945
01:11:17.097 --> 01:11:19.664
[tense music]

946
01:11:25.296 --> 01:11:26.764
[fire crackling]

947
01:11:26.864 --> 01:11:28.664
- You were well paid
for your information.


948
01:11:28.764 --> 01:11:31.630
Information that came
to be quite incorrect.


949
01:11:31.731 --> 01:11:33.931
I believed you were a
man who knew things.


950
01:11:34.030 --> 01:11:35.764
- And so I am.

951
01:11:37.197 --> 01:11:39.697
Only I never told
you nothing as fact.


952
01:11:39.797 --> 01:11:41.630
Only what I'd heard.

953
01:11:41.731 --> 01:11:43.864
I can't do no better than that.

954
01:11:43.963 --> 01:11:47.262
- You must do much better,
I am not to be disappointed.


955
01:11:47.362 --> 01:11:49.262
The man you claimed had
the items in his possession


956
01:11:49.362 --> 01:11:50.764
is now dead.

957
01:11:50.864 --> 01:11:53.630
His body stolen, his house
searched without result.


958
01:11:53.731 --> 01:11:56.097
I believe we can rule him out.

959
01:11:56.197 --> 01:11:57.864
- It wasn't him what got them.

960
01:11:59.229 --> 01:12:01.464
It was him they was got for.

961
01:12:02.797 --> 01:12:05.329
It was his wife
what bought them.


962
01:12:07.197 --> 01:12:08.797
It was his wife, I tell you.

963
01:12:08.897 --> 01:12:10.130
It was his wife.

964
01:12:10.229 --> 01:12:12.963
[dramatic music]

965
01:12:24.797 --> 01:12:26.831
- I thought a
disguise was in order,


966
01:12:26.930 --> 01:12:28.530
if we're staking out the place.

967
01:12:30.097 --> 01:12:30.963
- Right.

968
01:12:33.197 --> 01:12:34.797
- Well now I feel stupid.

969
01:12:37.329 --> 01:12:39.630
- I assure you, you've
never looked lovelier.


970
01:12:49.296 --> 01:12:52.329
- We'd be for it if
old Brammings caught
us sneaking about.


971
01:12:52.430 --> 01:12:54.130
- He's on his way to the ball.

972
01:12:54.229 --> 01:12:55.163
This place and
its people will be


973
01:12:55.262 --> 01:12:56.963
entirely gone from his thoughts.

974
01:12:58.630 --> 01:13:01.497
I feel we're always one step
behind what's happening.


975
01:13:01.597 --> 01:13:03.229
We hide in the cemetery,
they strike in the asylum.


976
01:13:03.329 --> 01:13:04.797
We watch over the dead,
they take the living.


977
01:13:04.896 --> 01:13:07.063
- Do you really think old
Brammings is in on it?


978
01:13:07.163 --> 01:13:08.430
- It's hard to believe.

979
01:13:08.530 --> 01:13:09.963
Yet he cares so little
for these people.


980
01:13:10.063 --> 01:13:11.996
- But you do though, don't you?

981
01:13:12.996 --> 01:13:15.363
You care for our lot.

982
01:13:17.564 --> 01:13:22.630
- I care a very great
deal for your lot.


983
01:13:24.863 --> 01:13:27.063
[patient whistling]

984
01:13:27.163 --> 01:13:28.296
- That's old Manic.

985
01:13:28.397 --> 01:13:31.197
Screams the place
down half the night.


986
01:13:31.296 --> 01:13:33.363
- That's certainly
very helpful, isn't it.


987
01:13:46.896 --> 01:13:49.097
- Quiet down now, love.

988
01:13:49.197 --> 01:13:50.630
Everything's all right.

989
01:13:50.731 --> 01:13:53.330
[gentle music]

990
01:13:53.430 --> 01:13:55.363
- I can't see a pattern here.

991
01:13:55.464 --> 01:13:56.664
They're taking both
the living and the dead


992
01:13:56.764 --> 01:13:58.297
with no discernible
buyer in sight.


993
01:13:58.397 --> 01:13:59.229
- I'm with Jasper.

994
01:13:59.330 --> 01:14:00.930
It's one of yours doing it.

995
01:14:01.030 --> 01:14:02.363
Look at who they're taking.

996
01:14:02.464 --> 01:14:05.363
It's only the poor, the
forsaken, except your father.


997
01:14:05.464 --> 01:14:06.697
He doesn't fit in.

998
01:14:06.796 --> 01:14:07.996
- No, I suppose not.

999
01:14:08.097 --> 01:14:10.097
- The rich look after
themselves, even in death.


1000
01:14:10.197 --> 01:14:11.430
Their crypts are
locked up tight,


1001
01:14:11.530 --> 01:14:13.764
their graves are
covered in cages.


1002
01:14:13.863 --> 01:14:15.497
I'm surprised your
father didn't have one.


1003
01:14:15.597 --> 01:14:16.697
He was rich enough.

1004
01:14:16.796 --> 01:14:18.497
- Mother was dead
set against it.


1005
01:14:18.597 --> 01:14:20.764
She's gone rather
strange since he died.


1006
01:14:20.863 --> 01:14:22.464
A bit Miss Haversham.

1007
01:14:22.564 --> 01:14:27.630
She didn't, she didn't
want him penned in.


1008
01:14:28.430 --> 01:14:29.497
- She's been here more often,

1009
01:14:29.597 --> 01:14:31.630
wandering in a
daze sort of thing.


1010
01:14:32.430 --> 01:14:34.297
- My mother's been here?

1011
01:14:34.397 --> 01:14:36.297
- Some of the girls
have spoken to her.


1012
01:14:36.397 --> 01:14:37.530
She's looked clear through them

1013
01:14:37.630 --> 01:14:39.597
as if she's not
seen them at all.


1014
01:14:40.796 --> 01:14:41.863
- We use your bodies.

1015
01:14:44.330 --> 01:14:48.197
- Still you need more,
to find your way back.


1016
01:14:49.763 --> 01:14:50.796
- Oh God.

1017
01:14:51.830 --> 01:14:52.731
- Eh?

1018
01:14:53.996 --> 01:14:55.564
- You need fresh flesh.

1019
01:14:58.097 --> 01:15:00.530
Living flesh closer to your own.

1020
01:15:03.097 --> 01:15:04.863
- You said, "We
use your bodies."


1021
01:15:04.963 --> 01:15:07.963
[dramatic music]

1022
01:15:08.063 --> 01:15:09.297
- William.

1023
01:15:11.363 --> 01:15:12.963
- Oh Mother!

1024
01:15:13.063 --> 01:15:16.697
[dramatic music continues]

1025
01:15:27.664 --> 01:15:28.397
[William grunts]

1026
01:15:34.397 --> 01:15:38.363
[dramatic music continues]

1027
01:15:58.830 --> 01:16:00.297
Father?

1028
01:16:05.164 --> 01:16:07.363
What in God's name has she done?

1029
01:16:08.464 --> 01:16:10.630
What in God's name
has she done to you?


1030
01:16:14.063 --> 01:16:15.330
- He doesn't know me.

1031
01:16:17.030 --> 01:16:18.464
His soul is lost.

1032
01:16:21.263 --> 01:16:22.530
- His soul is lost?

1033
01:16:24.663 --> 01:16:28.397
